entries.title: Cristiano Ronaldo signs with Saudi Arabian side Al-Nassr FC
entries.description: Cristiano Ronaldo has signed for Saudi Arabian team Al-Nassr FC, according to the club.

entries.title: Romanian court rules social media influencer Andrew Tate to be detained for 30 days
entries.description: A Romanian court has ruled social media influencer Andrew Tate will remain in custody for 30 days.

entries.title: UK expected to require travellers from China to provide negative COVID test
entries.description: The UK is expected to announce a requirement for travellers arriving from China to provide a negative pre-departure COVID test.

entries.title: 'The war changed everything': Ukraine's top performers forced to grapple war and music
entries.description: Slogans of solidarity with Ukraine have been spray-painted on walls, hung from banners and sung on stages across the world.

entries.title: Trump warns of 'horrible things for so many people' after his tax returns are released
entries.description: In response to the release of thousands of pages of his tax returns, former US president Donald Trump warned "horrible things" were to come, taking aim at "radical left Democrats".

entries.title: Former Pope Benedict XVI 'stable' and able to 'rest well' overnight, Vatican says
entries.description: Former Pope Benedict XVI is "stable" and was able to "rest well" last night, the Vatican has said.

entries.title: Greta Thunberg takes another swipe at Andrew Tate with pizza box jibe
entries.description: Greta Thunberg has dealt Andrew Tate another blow in the Twitter spat that has exploded this week, taunting him following his arrest in Romania.

entries.title: Indian cricket star 'dozed off' before fireball car crash
entries.description: Indian cricket star Rishabh Pant is facing the prospect of a lengthy injury spell after a horror car crash that forced him to punch his way out of the vehicle when it burst into flames.

entries.title: Spain becomes second European country to announce COVID restrictions for travellers from China
entries.description: Spain has become the second European country to announce new COVID restrictions for travellers from China following a surge in cases.

entries.title: Blair wanted Putin at 'top table' while he was PM despite officials' fears
entries.description: Tony Blair wanted Vladimir Putin to have a seat at the international "top table" during his time as prime minister, according to newly released official files.

entries.title: 'To play like Pele is to play like God': What other players said of the Brazilian great
entries.description: Brazil football great Pele has been praised all over the world following his death at age 82.

entries.title: Ousted Myanmar leader Aung San Suu Kyi jailed for another seven years
entries.description: The ousted leader of Myanmar, Aung San Suu Kyi, has been sentenced to a further seven years in prison for alleged corruption.

entries.title: Brazil begins three days of mourning after death of Pele
entries.description: Brazil has entered three days of mourning following the death of football superstar Pele.
